 "Landrein", "peopleAlsoViewed/21/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/21/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D03AQGiiqlm2RwH3w/profile-displayphoto-crop_800_800/B4DZyz5G0RJoAM-/0/1772544620232?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=V0nGWnOvHbgO3-pPjbrKWGAG11S9-1eWv7SpAw61hZY", "peopleAlsoViewed/21/public_identifier": "patrice-landrein-6b515567", "peopleAlsoViewed/21/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAA4U9qkB7I_r5hWfcauj8-_tEbMStalKapY", "peopleAlsoViewed/22/entity_urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAACEm7ZoB4LppQmARU9y7GOuVjqjvT2EGDpE", "peopleAlsoViewed/22/first_name": "Prachoom", "peopleAlsoViewed/22/follower_count": "52", "peopleAlsoViewed/22/headline": "General Manager at Dusit Thani Laguna Phuket", "peopleAlsoViewed/22/last_name": "Tantiprasertsul", "peopleAlsoViewed/22/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/22/public_identifier": "prachoom-tantiprasertsul-73632a136", "peopleAlsoViewed/22/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAACEm7ZoB4LppQmARU9y7GOuVjqjvT2EGDpE", "peopleAlsoViewed/23/entity_urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAJk7BYBQoJOQkTbvqhjm6YWKas_8C6wbdY", "peopleAlsoViewed/23/first_name": "Luca", "peopleAlsoViewed/23/follower_count": "0", "peopleAlsoViewed/23/headline": "Hotel Manager", "peopleAlsoViewed/23/last_name": "Forges Davanzati", "peopleAlsoViewed/23/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/23/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQGqkdpalkYdtA/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1715707756609?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=Gs9x7ElNeWK948ZrhF865ElzEFVA1WnsAufRX8HvEMY", "peopleAlsoViewed/23/public_identifier": "luca-forges-davanzati-78655111", "peopleAlsoViewed/23/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAAJk7BYBQoJOQkTbvqhjm6YWKas_8C6wbdY", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/entity_urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAANePC0B_N-djFOJBmSbgL9jGLwOH0y7zNM", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/first_name": "Ammarawadee", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/follower_count": "670", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/headline": "General Manager driving commercial success in hospitality management / Special Lecturer for Marketing and Finance For Non-Financial", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/last_name": "Cheowit", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/premium": "true", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQH6OVGoSkoqyw/profile-displayphoto-crop_800_800/B56ZrZDx8qIcAI-/0/1764578243811?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=xkHOV6hi6Y9nZwuvrvfpChm1u5nG9aZ3aFm8CVxyum0", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/public_identifier": "amma-cheowit007", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAANePC0B_N-djFOJBmSbgL9jGLwOH0y7zNM", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/entity_urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABqaZRUBh-hQ2BRYSqGvLNc-r2vzp4n_x7c", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/first_name": "Mark", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/follower_count": "2290", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/headline": "Head of F&B @ The NoMad London", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/last_name": "Lee", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E03AQG8uqb3Oznasw/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/B4EZd3z6ZZH0Ac-/0/1750061787660?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=H1qSZfpNu3YPV_gzEe4O9ZxY0XrfF4GEV_Z4n08p7oc", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/public_identifier": "markalee1", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAABqaZRUBh-hQ2BRYSqGvLNc-r2vzp4n_x7c", "profilePic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQEQuNQJUOq1aw/profile-displayphoto-crop_800_800/B56ZirtbC3HcAI-/0/1755227468936?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=AUki8xuDvL9XNOWHoiK_CRkArcARV6DndAInOepc1Rw", "profilePicHighQuality": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQEQuNQJUOq1aw/profile-displayphoto-crop_800_800/B56ZirtbC3HcAI-/0/1755227468936?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=AUki8xuDvL9XNOWHoiK_CRkArcARV6DndAInOepc1Rw", "publicIdentifier": "samir-wildemann", "recommendations/0/context": "Samir managed Oliver directly", "recommendations/0/date": "October 31, 2025", "recommendations/0/description": "It was an absolute pleasure to have Oliver serve as the Hotel Manager during my time at the Siam Kempinski Hotel Bangkok. In this crucial role, he was not just a colleague but a true pillar of the hotel's leadership, and his impact was felt across every department.\n\nOliver possesses a rare blend of strategic vision and hands-on operational excellence. While he expertly managed the day-to-day complexities of a world-class hotel, his focus never wavered from driving business results and elevating guest satisfaction. He leads with a calm authority and genuine authenticity that immediately earns the trust and respect of his team, his peers, and ownership alike.\n\nWhat truly sets Oliver apart is his unwavering integrity and his sincere, people-first approach to leadership. He fosters a culture of excellence and collaboration, always ensuring his team feels supported and empowered. Beyond the walls of the hotel, he is a proud ambassador for the brand, as evidenced by his active role in the broader hospitality community in Bangkok.\n\nI wholeheartedly endorse Oliver. He is a values-driven leader, a strategic thinker, and an asset to any organization. Any team would be fortunate to have him.", "recommendations/0/name": "Oliver Schnatz", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Hospitality Strategy & Operations Leader – 20 Years’ Experience Across World-Renowned Luxury Hotel Brands", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/oliver-schnatz-hospitality/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAAqTDMBKBclM1kk-9osLcQ4QrzUjRyQgs4", "recommendations/1/context": "Samir managed Clay directly", "recommendations/1/date": "October 6, 2022", "recommendations/1/description": "I had the pleasure to work with Clay when I was the Vice President Operations of Fusion Hotel Group. Clay stood out with his management style and his ability to adapt to very unique sets of challenges as his posting at the resort was only a few month after the property had opened and it coincided with beginning of the Pandemic. He was spot on with the strategy and his actions to move the hotel in its opening year onto the right track and managed to also establish a strong relationship with the owning company. \nI would have no hesitations to recommend Clay to any group which are looking for a seasoned entrepreneur turned hotelier.", "recommendations/1/name": "Clay C.", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "General Manager | Pre-Opening Specialist | Hospitality Entrepreneur | Experienced Luxury Hotelier across 4 countries", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/clayclayton/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAkgvi8Ba814hAiNfIHUdM0vHSbD70Pb8Rw", "recommendations/2/context": "Samir was Emile's client", "recommendations/2/date": "October 3, 2021", "recommendations/2/description": "We deal with many suppliers every day, and if someone stands out, he definitely leaves a mark. Emile looked after our hotel group here in Vietnam while at AIM and he was a person one could count on at all times, but what stood out with Emile was his ‘Yes I Can’ attitude and his ability to outperform each and every time. \nEmile, on a personal note, we wish you all the best in your new role and just keep on doing what you do best! It clearly works!", "recommendations/2/name": "Emile van Zyl", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Building a Discord CRM, Community Relationship Management Software, CEEJAY by Community Studios.", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/emile-van-zyl-b49750140/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAACJIL2kBZ3bBcarQEXUGteqiAK2i5T-MLLk", "recommendations/3/context": "Peter Andrew was Samir's client", "recommendations/3/date": "March 7, 2021", "recommendations/3/description": "Recommendations\nI am writing in regards to my professional relationship with Peter Mantello, who I regularly contracted as a media service supplier for two 5-Star Hotel properties that I managed in the period from 2002 to 2007, namely Le Royal Méridien Baan Taling Ngam in Koh Samui, Thailand, and the Pan Pacific Hotel in Bangkok. Peter came to my attention in 2002, after being hired to create several large multi-media projects for Le Méridien’s Regional Head Office here in Bangkok. His company represented all of Le Méridien’s properties in Thailand as well as Cambodia. Having had a chance to work with him during his period, I was extremely impressed with the quality of his Company’s work and the high degree of professionalism by which he directed his staff. When I moved to Pan Pacific Bangkok, I contracted Peter’s company to do several large media projects as well as employing him to do our brochure photography. During this time, Peter’s company designed an innovative 3D interactive map which we used on our website. Peter’s attitude toward his clients was always first-class. But what I appreciated most during our professional relationship was his high degree of care, creativity and quality that he injected into each project, no matter how small. I would not hesitate to contract Peter in the future should he be interested in doing professional commercial media work for us again.", "recommendations/3/name": "Peter Andrew Mantello", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "Researcher/Artist/Consultant", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/peter-andrew-mantello-45b77216b/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAACiDiwcBTotawWy57Fb9y5NvS_O6YwkpjJw", "recommendations/4/context": "Samir managed Jee Hoong directly", "recommendations/4/date": "October 2, 2019", "recommendations/4/description": "I had the pleasure to work with Jee Hoong when I was the General Manager for the Siam Kempinski Hotel Bangkok, as well as Area VP of Operations. He was one of the most incredible Directors of Sales & Marketing I came across in my career. Always spot on when it came to strategy and the way he managend to position the property in the early days after opening has been instrumental to positioning the hotel into the upper level of this very competitive market, making it the RevPAR leader in the city. The team Jee Hoong surrounded himself with was one of the most loyal and dedicated I have seen and the key to all the success. I would have no hesitation in recommending Jee Hoong and I wish him continued success in his career.", "recommendations/4/name": "Jee Hoong Tan", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "Agile Leader | Global Commercial Strategist | Operational Excellence | Passionate Hotelier", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jee-hoong-tan-7b33237/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAFLDrcB3yGD-nPqwfKl2l3A2AP08oj-a4g", "recommendations/5/context": "Samir managed James directly", "recommendations/5/date": "February 5, 2018", "recommendations/5/description": "James exemplifies everything you want in a top Executive Chef: highly talented, with a passion for culinary excellence and with an unrelenting dedication to his job.\nDuring our time together in this property, we have seen a complete revamp of the gastronomic offerings in two of our three outlets and the overall food quality has increased tremendously throughout the hotel. This was achieved without straining the food cost, by streamlining our food production and rigorously controlling our purchases while educating his team about the importance of their roles in maintaining our food quality.\nDuring his tenure, we were also very fortunate to have seen our signature restaurant ‘Sra Bua by Kiin Kiin’ being awarded one Michelin Star when the guide was launched in Bangkok in December 2017.\n\nI valued greatly his contributions during the two years together in Bangkok and I would also be delighted to work with James at some level again...and sincerely hope the situation arises.", "recommendations/5/name": "James Norman", "recommendations/5/subtitle": "General manager - Nutfield Priory Hotel & Spa", "recommendations/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jamesjnorman/", "recommendations/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAElWnoBjurEzyD5QStCIZ0bXRAWpge6NlI", "recommendations/6/context": "Samir managed Andreas directly", "recommendations/6/date": "February 5, 2018", "recommendations/6/description": "Andreas joined my team in mid 2017 as Hotel Manager and it was a true pleasure to have made his acquaintance, not only as an executive committee member, but also on a personal level. \nA true hotelier, able to integrate into the organisation in lightning speed where he managed in a very short time to address shortcomings and implementing very successful new initiatives. He has done an incredible job in both dealing with the ongoing tasks and managing the day to day operations of this luxury city resort. In a nutshell, I found in Andreas a very innovative and charismatic professional with very sound integrity. \nRegretfully we only worked together for a short time. His young career is only in the starting blocks ... and there is a secret hope to be able to work together again!", "recommendations/6/name": "Andreas Magnus", "recommendations/6/subtitle": "General Manager | Kempinski Palace Engelberg and Frutt Mountain Resort managed by Kempinski", "recommendations/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/andreas-magnus-35185116/", "recommendations/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAANUHa0BHkVeC9EFojp-990qbKD6PqsXnKA", "recommendations/7/context": "Samir was Eric's client", "recommendations/7/date": "November 25, 2017", "recommendations/7/description": "I had the pleasure working on a truly exciting project during my tenure as General Manager and Senior Vice President Operations for South East Asia at the Siam Kempinski Hotel Bangkok.\n\nA brief introduction on how we initially joined forces with Eric and his team on this project. At Siam Kempinski we are blessed with having close to 2000 pieces of artwork on display and without exception these works have been created specifically for the hotel by some of Thailand’s most talented artists. It was our intention to allow a broader audience to access these works of art and to showcase to a global audience the breadth of creative talent that exists in Thailand. Hence the idea of an online gallery was born. \n\nFrom the beginning of our conversation, it was clear that Eric had a true passion for art and culture, and combining this with his vision, remarkable energy as well as skills in business development we were confident to have found the right partner for this project.\n\nEric, through his company Art Consulting Thailand, came up with an innovative concept to build a social network marketplace, enabling Thai artists and designers to connect to organizations, in order to give them sustainable opportunities, in line with our initial commitment to support the nations artists as they strive to gain and retain local and international recognition. To operate and monitor this platform, Art Consulting Thailand has developed a technology which we have incorporated into our project. This allows us to connect with a much broader audience interested in Thai Art and Culture, giving us and the artists the potential of reaching an audience of millions of enthusiasts.\n\nThe final result has certainly exceeded our initial expectations. Art Consulting Thailand has provided in time, in a very professional and enthusiastic way, a designed platform, which is now Siam Kempinski Art Gallery (www.siamkempinski-artgallery.com), showcasing specific academic content related to Siam Kempinski’s art collection and history, biographies, photos, videos and interviews of artists (18 in total at this stage) and a complete descriptions of each artwork on display (57 in public areas). Now, any of our clients enjoying art in the hotel has access to our platform, via wall tag barcodes, and through this learning more about our collection and more importantly, the artists.\n\nI know that Eric is currently looking for new clients and investors to speed up the growth of his company and to secure this ambitious and innovative project (Art Consulting Thailand, Silapix and Silasoft, the Sila ecosystem as Eric names it).\nIt has been a pleasure working with Eric on this Project and I thank all those involved, including our own and very dedicated Marketing team for their patience and dedication.", "recommendations/7/name": "Eric Monteil", "recommendations/7/subtitle": "Founder of Rock/Around/Siam & Siamnity | Bangkok-based boutique travel agency | Bespoke journeys & private tours | Off-the-beaten-path immersion | Exploring Thailand’s cultural heritage", "recommendations/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ericmonteil/", "recommendations/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAATAWYBhRABiDNF8RTvS31b2UXWxpEaiN8", "recommendations/8/context": "Samir managed Takafumi directly", "recommendations/8/date": "August 15, 2016", "recommendations/8/description": "\"Consistently, during Hikita-san's employment with The Okura Prestige Bangkok, I have been most impressed with his strong work ethics and consistency even during difficult times. Under his leadership in Revenue Management the hotel positioned itself in the top 5 in the Bangkok market in terms of RevPAR, which was an impressive achievement for a newly opened hotel in a very competitive environment.\"", "recommendations/8/name": "Takafumi Hikita", "recommendations/8/subtitle": "Founder & CEO, Stayand Inc", "recommendations/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/takafumi-hikita/", "recommendations/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAU7FywB7-FutH3pgRvevCII-KDYGWpiM7s", "recommendations/9/context": "Michael Paul was Samir's client", "recommendations/9/date": "March 18, 2015", "recommendations/9/description": "The Teamcraft teambuilding program Mike conducted for 50 of our senior management members was not only inspiring but mind-set changing. We all walked away energised and engaged and the feedback from all participants was excellent. Mike managed to design a very creative programme with strong messages in line with our business priorities and the workshop gave everyone simple tools enabling us to move from ‘Very Good’ to ‘Excellent’! Back at work the initiatives are in motion and his programme has unlocked our mind-sets and make us see the possibilities in impossibilities. Thank you Mike, it was a joy to have been introduced to this programme.", "recommendations/9/name": "Michael Paul Stephens", "recommendations/9/subtitle": "Passionate Learning and Development Professional", "recommendations/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/michael-paul-stephens/", "recommendations/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAHy6CkBB4sJBm5PLeVwzOtq8TaX2_5TVgY", "recommendations/10/context": "Samir managed Helene directly", "recommendations/10/date": "June 6, 2013", "recommendations/10/description": "I worked with Helene at The Pan Pacific Bangkok and I would work with her any time any day again. \n\nHelene joined us from our owners property in Manila and it was her first senior manager role in which she settled with great ease. Her perspective of any challenge was exceptional and well communicated, making her an effective observer, decision maker and implementer; it has been a pleasure to work with Helene who inspired the people around her to learn, grow, and develop into better hoteliers and restaurateurs under her leadership. \n\nHer energy, initiative and creativity combined with planning, fiscal insight, operating savvyness and her past experience of opening, what was to become Manilas most talked about dining venue, made her the ideal candidate to oversee and prepare the upcoming renovation of our Bangkok’s F&B outlets. The designers (SPIN), being the same team as in Manila, had also only praise for her and this made Helen an ideal candidate at the time. \nHer genuine passion, loyalty and commitment to the team and the task at hand, were remarkable and her knowledge and dedication to consistently deliver the highest quality results for both guests, property and company were very impressive to witness in a person at the beginning of her career. \n\nKnowing that Helene has now set up her own company, dedicated to sharing what she does best, I am confident that she will not be disappointing anyone that places trust in her services. All the very best Helene!", "recommendations/10/name": "Helene Lauras", "recommendations/10/subtitle": "Responsable Stratégie et Solutions Occupants/ VINCI Facilities", "recommendations/10/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/helenelaurasbordeaux/", "recommendations/10/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAA28SfsBD7qiHbYyd-C0jN0fLZlRyHMQEgc", "recommendations/11/context": "Samir managed Prasarn directly", "recommendations/11/date": "October 31, 2012", "recommendations/11/description": "During my time at The Pan Pacific Bangkok Khun Prasarn held the position of Rooms Division Manager/Front of House Manager. \n\nWhilst I have been working with Khun Prasarn I have always found him to be a hardworking and dedicated member of the management team. His commitment to his responsibilities has contributed greatly to the smooth operation of the hotel. He has a very pleasant personality and is always of smart appearance.\n\nI firmly believe that Khun Prasarn has the necessary knowledge and ambition to add value to anyone’s business and I believe that he has the right character and personality to be able to adapt to many sorts of environments and challenges.\n\nShould you require any further information I would be more than happy to help.", "recommendations/11/name": "Prasarn Thaitae", "recommendations/11/subtitle": "General Manager", "recommendations/11/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/prasarn-thaitae-6b467b54/", "recommendations/11/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAt9TSgBfrG03OTl70JncSfoZWn8hiseyO0", "recommendations/12/context": "Samir was David's client", "recommendations/12/date": "July 25, 2012", "recommendations/12/description": "To Who it May Concern\nAs the General Manager of this prestigious new hotel project in Bangkok it was my task to source for a professional creative agency that could assist us in the design and fabrication of our hotels collaterals and also advertising material that would be in line with our customers high expectations. Having had a free hand in terms of design with very flexible brand standards this would have obviously been an interesting project for anyone to manage.\nHaving reviewed our options we met David and his team and after having listened to him and viewed their website and portfolio we were convinced that The Creative Partnership were the right company as we were impressed by their professional approach, their creative ideas and their technical as well as specialist knowledge, and most of all,  their understanding of our needs. Opening a luxury property such as The Okura Prestige, needed a partner of the highest calibre and we needed to be confident that we would have a professional partner on board with the resultant work meeting also value for money.\nWe are and remain extremely pleased with the resulting work and David and his very professional team managed to interpret our ideas exactly by creating work that had a modern and clean professional look in line with our requirements. Throughout the project The Creative Partnership were always ready to suggest new ideas that would add value to the Hotel and what impresses me personally most was their passion to please the client by providing at every occasion numerous options to choose from for every task that had been assigned to them. \nDuring a hotel opening there are obviously endless matters to focus on and I was able to trust and be guided by their creative judgment, allowing myself and my team to focus our input elsewhere where it was needed. \nI would have no hesitations in recommending The Creative Partnership - for their customer service, business acumen, for taking the burden off me, for progressing the project and for understanding the clients requirements at every instance.\nYours sincerely\n\nSamir R. Wildemann \nGeneral Manager   \nThe Okura Prestige Bangkok", "recommendations/12/name": "David Blowers", "recommendations/12/subtitle": "Senior Partner at The Creative Partnership Thailand", "recommendations/12/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/david-blowers-334b0131/", "recommendations/12/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAa_nJgBqFafndCrNRzxyD1WoFa8DnwQIo0", "recommendations/13/context": "Samir was senior to Kan but didn't manage Kan directly", "recommendations/13/date": "July 29, 2011", "recommendations/13/description": "Chef Bright joined the Radisson pre-opening team of the 436 room and 180 residences project in Sathorn in February 2009 and has proven to be a very reliable team member. His skills and the careful practice of leadership have contributed substantially to the successful launch of the complex. His meticulous and methodical approach towards his work and his strong commitment are only a few of his many exceptional qualities and on more than one occasion they have helped him overcome and successfully solve operational challenges. I value greatly his contributions to the operation and especially the opening and it has been a pleasure working with him.", "recommendations/13/name": "Kan Bright San", "recommendations/13/subtitle": "Ad Lib Hotel and Innovation Center Khon Kaen", "recommendations/13/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/kan-bright-san-b59b0327/", "recommendations/13/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAWuTrUB0PIlJlZeoCRG2jguGcUb7S_b4Ag", "recommendations/14/context": "Samir worked with Marco Ronnie on the same team", "recommendations/14/date": "December 23, 2010", "recommendations/14/description": "I wish to endorse Marco, a friend and colleague for the past 3 years. While we were opening the Radisson Sathorn in Bangkok, Marco has been an excellent colleague from down-the-road, always supportive and displaying an excellent yes-I-can attitude which has certainly contributed to the successful opening of our hotel. It was a pleasure to have had this close working relationship within the same company and city! I wish him the best of luck with his new assignment.\nSincerely\nSamir\n\nSamir R Wildemann\nGeneral Manager\nHotel Okura Bangkok", "recommendations/14/name": "Marco Ronnie Seiler", "recommendations/14/subtitle": "Eidg. Dipl. Hotelier & Restaurateur HF", "recommendations/14/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/marcoseiler/", "recommendations/14/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAACl0jMBcybbZzrhnxp0ZRsT7hoW9u53gAs", "recommendations/15/context": "Samir managed Philippe directly", "recommendations/15/date": "November 9, 2008", "recommendations/15/description": "Having worked with Philippe in Koh Samui and having seen the results he produced, I would not hesitate to recommend him to any future employer, and that without any hesitation. I can be contacted at any time for further references.", "recommendations/15/name": "Philippe Tardieu", "recommendations/15/subtitle": "Global Luxury Hospitality and Food Retail Executive | Consultant | Dots connector | Business development | Franchising | Multi-projects mgt | Turn Around | Strategist | Customer experience-centric | Proud dad", "recommendations/15/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ptardieu/", "recommendations/15/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGJvNwBHwZHdDnnq2uQaKZpdS6bi1Sr4ic", "recommendations/16/context": "Samir was senior to Tommy Chi-On but didn't manage Tommy Chi-On directly", "recommendations/16/date": "July 15, 2008", "recommendations/16/description": "This is in response to a request for a letter of recommendation for Tommy lai who worked under me during my tiem as General Manager at le Royal Meridien Baan Taling Ngam. Tommy is a hard-working self-starter who invariably understands exactly what Sales and Marketing is all about from the outset, and how to get it running effectively even in very competitive market conditions. I found Tommy to be a resourceful, creative, and solution-oriented person who was frequently able to come up with new and innovative approaches to challenges.\nBased on my experience working with him I can unreservedly recommend Tommy to anyone looking for a Sales & Marketing Specialist. If you would like further elaboration, feel free to contact me.", "recommendations/16/name": "Tommy Chi-On Lai", "recommendations/16/subtitle": "@Oracle - Digital AI Transformation x Hospitality x Sustainability", "recommendations/16/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/tommylai/", "recommendations/16/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEVXvMBTjB9c8q1vagcGShfvEKLcvyoUms", "recommendations/17/context": "Samir was Harsh's client", "recommendations/17/date": "July 15, 2008", "recommendations/17/description": "This is in response to a request for a letter of recommendation for Harsh Adhyapak who worked directly for me from August 2004 until my departure from the company in April 2008.\nHarsh is a hard-working self-starter who invariably understands exactly what telemarketing and sales is all about from the outset, and how to get it running effectively even in very competitive market conditions. I found Harsh to be a resourceful, creative, and solution-oriented person who was frequently able to come up with new and innovative approaches to challenges.\nBased on my experience working with him I can unreservedly recommend Harsh to anyone looking for a telemarketing specialist. If you would like further elaboration, feel free to contact me.", "recommendations/17/name": "Harsh A.", "recommendations/17/subtitle": "CEO and Founder at Equinox Marketing Co., Ltd. - Provider of Exceptional Hotel Loyalty Programs", "recommendations/17/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/harsh-a-3a18591/", "recommendations/17/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAABNw-kBZQUe4sMvan7-tNKZ2uikibRUKJw", "recommendations/18/context": "Samir was senior to Jutta but didn't manage Jutta directly", "recommendations/18/date": "February 17, 2006", "recommendations/18/description": "Jutta and I worked very closely together when I was GM at 2 Le Meridien Resort properties in Thailand (both members of LHW). She has done a fantastic job in terms of Rev Management, on-line training and development. We would never have achieved 2 digit growth figures without her input! Her passion for the job and her commitment is what has impressed me most.", "recommendations/18/name": "Jutta Moore", "recommendations/18/subtitle": "Revenue Management Consultant, Travel Tech Advisor, Commercial Hotel Management, Project Manager, Interim Management", "recommendations/18/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/juttamoore/", "recommendations/18/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAAwRfwBEGt158jsTiLs3gJGvFHKKdiV7dE", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Michael managed Samir directly", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "February 5, 2018", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "Samir is an exceptional hotelier. Besides extremely high expectations of his teams and his property he is a highly skilled marketeer with a unique sense of his competitive environment and his hotel’s position in the competitive set. \nHe is affable, constantly present and a delight to be around. \nHis highly trained eye spots everything and his team admire his calm demeanour even under pressure. \nI would work with him anytime should an opportunity arise. ", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Michael Sagild", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "Co-Founder & President at Cloud Collective", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/michael-sagild-b332b17/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAFKEBcB3xTKyf-QSaN3Qls1kxqyFpBEJTc", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Helene reported directly to Samir", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "May 13, 2013", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "When Samir hired me at the Pan Pacific Bangkok I was very young and quite impress by the role I had to take up on. The support and confidence that Samir showed me was just the sign of a great General Manager. Samir is a very strong GM with a great understanding of what true hospitality means towards both his guest and his team.", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Helene Lauras", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Responsable Stratégie et Solutions Occupants/ VINCI Facilities", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/helenelaurasbordeaux/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAA28SfsBD7qiHbYyd-C0jN0fLZlRyHMQEgc", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Prasarn reported directly to Samir", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "October 31, 2012", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "I had a pleasure to work with him at Pan Pacific Bangkok. He is the professional GM with high ability in term of hotel management. His leader skill and working style was satisfied me, kindness, fair, always polite and well understand both of client and his subordinate.\n\nI thoroughly enjoyed during time working with Samir and very appreciated if time cross again", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Prasarn Thaitae", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "General Manager", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/prasarn-thaitae-6b467b54/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAt9TSgBfrG03OTl70JncSfoZWn8hiseyO0", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "Harsh reported directly to Samir", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "December 9, 2009", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "Samir's work style and overall perspective towards micro or macro managing challenges has a genuinely broad based foundation. Working with Samir is intellectaully stimulating and professionally gratifying. Avenues for growth are always guaranteed for deserving candidates while you work for or with Samir. It was a pleasure to have the opportunity to work and report to him during his tenure as General Manager of Pan Pacific Bangkok.", "recommendationsReceived/3/name": "Harsh A.", "recommendationsReceived/3/subtitle": "CEO and Founder at Equinox Marketing Co., Ltd. - Provider of Exceptional Hotel Loyalty Programs", "recommendationsReceived/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/harsh-a-3a18591/", "recommendationsReceived/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAABNw-kBZQUe4sMvan